Subject: [CLA-2003:760] Conectiva Security Announcement - mplayer


-----BEGIN PGP SIGNED MESSAGE-----
Hash: SHA1

- --------------------------------------------------------------------------
CONECTIVA LINUX SECURITY ANNOUNCEMENT 
- --------------------------------------------------------------------------

PACKAGE   : mplayer
SUMMARY   : Remote buffer overflow vulnerability
DATE      : 2003-10-06 12:37:00
ID        : CLA-2003:760
RELEVANT
RELEASES  : 9

- -------------------------------------------------------------------------

DESCRIPTION
 MPlayer is a multimedia player that supports several video and audio
 codecs.
 
 Hernï¿½n Otero found[2] a remote buffer overflow vulnerability[3] in a
 function which parses ASX streaming headers. An attacker can exploit
 this vulnerability to potentially execute arbitrary code with the
 privileges of the user who is running mplayer by using a specially
 crafted ASF file (which can be served remotely).
 
 The Common Vulnerabilities and Exposures project (cve.mitre.org) has
 assigned the name CAN-2003-0835[3] to this issue.


SOLUTION
 All mplayer users should upgrade.
 
 
 REFERENCES:
 1.http://www.securityfocus.com/archive/1/339330
 2.http://www.securityfocus.com/archive/1/339193
 3.http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CAN-2003-0835


